# Cursor rules — PFMS

The canonical agent context for this repo is **`AGENTS.md`** (a symlink to `CLAUDE.md`).
Read it first. It contains the stack, conventions, the data-isolation rule, known gotchas,
and the env-var list.

## Before any task
1. **Read** `AGENTS.md`, then the doc map it points to in `.agent/docs/`:
   - `.agent/docs/README.md` — index
   - `.agent/docs/architecture.md` — system architecture & data flow
   - `.agent/docs/frontend-design.md` — UI/UX & design system
   - `.agent/docs/features/<feature>.md` — per-feature schema & actions
2. **Verify** your plan matches the documented architecture and patterns.
3. **Update** the relevant docs (and `CLAUDE.md`) in the same change if you make them obsolete.

## Non-negotiables (full list in AGENTS.md)
- Every Prisma query MUST be scoped by the authenticated `userId`.
- AI/API keys are server-side only — never ship them to the client.
- Validate all input with Zod; remember `.optional()` rejects `null` from `FormData`.
